      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, the important thing is that when we do |a-b|, a and b are in the same color space.\n\n|a-b| itself isn\u0027t _really_ a color, so it\u0027s probably fine to just treat as a plain old number. But if the image package weren\u0027t so... minimalist, I do think we\u0027d probably want to tag the diff itself with the same profile so we document what our diffs like \"1 bit difference in red channel, 4 bit difference in green channel\" mean if it ever comes down to a deep debugging investigation.",
